cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with computer vision techniques for estimating driver gaze, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also addresses human-computer interaction (cs.HC) by focusing on the driver's attention level and situational awareness. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for image-to-image translation and the incorporation of a gaze classifier and gaze consistency loss suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with real-world data and driving conditions, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
